Hello,
I am aware this is not the beta discussion thread, but I feel I have a more universal problem with one of our machines (that I need for a team meeting this evening).

What happened…
As far as I recall, WPILIB 2020, and 2021 was working on this computer. I installed the beta (WPILib 2022.1.1 Beta 2 Release).

I have the beta running on my personal machine, but I wanted to give people the opportunity to try it for our Romi build this evening.

Since installing, all of my builds in any version (2021, 2022, etc.) fail with the following error…

Error: Could not find or load main class org.gradle.wrapper.GradleWrapperMain    
Caused by: java.lang.ClassNotFoundException: org.gradle.wrapper.GradleWrapperMain
The terminal process "cmd.exe /d /c gradlew build   -Dorg.gradle.java.home="C:\Users\Public\wpilib\2021\jdk"" terminated with exit code: 1.

Terminal will be reused by tasks, press any key to close it.

I did install all of these on a Windows machine and in the public folder so all users could use it. I also installed the 2022 version from a flash drive (oops), and I cleaned out the hard drive prior (so may have accidentally deleted a dependancy for gradle).

Anyway, I am wondering if anyone has any idea about how to fix it and how to avoid breaking builds on our other machines if I try this on them. I also tried uninstalling 2022 and reinstalling ti to no avail.

Edit: I know the error is for v2021, but as I said, I get it in all the builds. I think the build number changes, but will check.

This error usually occurs when the gradle/wrapper/gradle-wrapper.jar is missing from your robot project. Can you confirm that this file (along with the gradle-wrapper.properties) exists in your project in that directory?

Yes, it is there. There is also a gradle-wrapper.properties file.
…

Just because it is there, does not mean gradle can find it. In a complete DOH!!! moment, I realized the issue was that the folder I was using as my upper-level project folder had a caret in it.

I am leaving this here as we have been repeatedly burned by this issue (I should have known). Thank you @Prateek_M for your help. I am not sure I would have figured it out without it.

I think it may. I think it goes for many non-letter or number characters. I think this includes spaces and apostrophes. It bit us first while we were remote and a student was on Zoom trying to program a Romi. His build folder was on onedrive.

Another thing that could affect your issue is hidden files and folders.

I assume the main issue with all of these things is that Wondows handles path and file names in an unusual manner conpared to Unix.

Your project should absolutely work with spaces and such.

However, onedrive will actually delete your files (only locally!) if their in that folder and aren’t directly accessed. It’s a space saving mechanism and is enabled by default. It might be better in something like https://docs.wpilib.org/stacktrace
